Class Templates:

This directory contains a set of class templates that are defined in 
namespace Pscf::Rp and are used in the program-level namespaces Pscf::Rpc 
and Rpg to create closely analogous pairs of classes used in different 
programs.  Instantiations of each class template in namespace Pscf::Rp 
are used as base classes for corresponding instantiations of two closely 
analogous class templates defined in Pscf::Rpc and Pscf::Rpg. Generally, 
the base class template in Pscf::Rp and the derived class templates in 
Pscf::Rpc and Rpg::Rpg all share the same name. For example, each 
instantiation of the template <int D> class Pscf::Rpc::System with an 
integer value D=1, 2, or 3 is derived from an instantiation of a class 
template defined in the Pscf::Rp namespace that is also named "System". 

Types classes as template arguments:

All of the templates defined in namespace Pscf::Rp take the dimension D of 
space as an integer template parameter. Most also take a class parameter 
named "T" as an additional parameter. In instantiations of such templates,
the argument associated with parameter T should either be a class template
instantiation Pscf::Rpc::Types<D> of the template defined in file 
src/rpc/system/Types.h, for instantiations used in namespace Pscf::Rpc, 
or an instantiation Pscf::Rpg::Types<D> of the template defined in file 
src/rpg/system/Types.h, for instantiations used in namespace Pscf::Rpg.  
The "Types" class templates defined in the Pscf::Rpc and Pscf::Rpg 
program-level namespaces each take the spatial dimension D as a single
template parameter, and define a set of typename aliases for classes used 
only in the enclosing program-level namespace for the specified value of 
D. Typename aliases defined in each such "Types" class are referred to 
in the implementation of class templates defined in Pscf::Rp to create 
generic class definitions that can be adapted for use in either pscf_rpc 
or pscf_rpg by simply using a different "Types" class as a template 
argument. As an example, consider the class template instantiation 
Pscf::Rpc::System<3>, which is the type of the main system object used 
in the pscf_rpc CPU program for problems involving three-dimensional 
fields. The required class is derived from the instantiation 
Pscf::Rp::System<3, Pscf::Rpc::Types<3> > of the System class template 
defined in namespace Rp, using an argument T=Pscf::Rpc::Types<3>.

Subdirectories:

The src/rp directory has the subjectories listed below, given a 
structure analogous to that of the src/rpc and src/rpg directories:

  
field/      - fields and spatial domain
fts/        - partial saddle-point field theoretic simulation (PS-FTS)
scft/       - self-consistent field theory (SCFT)
solvers/    - modified diffusion equation (MDE) solvers
system/     - main System class template

